## 5) KPI set (v1)

Track these weekly:

1. **Decision quality**
   - `% resolved_within_sla`
   - `% reopened` (lower is better)
2. **Execution efficiency**
   - median `time_to_first_action_minutes`
3. **Trust / adoption**
   - `% operator_override` (watch both very high and near-zero)
4. **Stability**
   - incident rate after decision changes
5. **Learning velocity**
   - number of validated insights shipped per week

Guardrails:
- Never degrade SLA metric by >3% week-over-week.
- If incident rate rises >1.5x baseline, auto-trigger rollback review.

---

## 6) Data contracts & storage

- Log format: `JSONL`, append-only
- Retention:
  - hot: 30 days
  - warm: 180 days
  - cold archive: 1 year
- Required IDs:
  - `event_id` (uuid)
  - `entity_id` (task/issue/item id)
  - `loop_id`
  - `policy_version`
- Correlation:
  - all events for a decision must share `entity_id` + `loop_id`

Recommended paths:
- `data/oaml/events-YYYY-MM.jsonl`
- `data/oaml/weekly-summaries/YYYY-WW.md`
- `docs/policies/task-priority.md`
- `docs/changelog/decision-policy.md`

---

## 7) Weekly operating ritual (30 min)

Agenda:

1. **Observe recap (5 min)**  
   Volume, anomalies, missing telemetry.

2. **Measure review (10 min)**  
   KPI deltas vs prior week and baseline.

3. **Learn extraction (10 min)**  
   Identify 1–3 high-confidence patterns.

4. **Update + Improve decisions (5 min)**  
   Approve exactly one policy change unless urgent.

Outputs required:
- Weekly summary note
- Policy/kb version bump
- Rollout decision (ship / hold / rollback)

---

## 8) Change management

Every decision-policy change must include:

- Hypothesis
- Expected KPI impact
- Risk assessment
- Rollback condition
- Owner
- Effective date/time

Template:
```md
Change ID: DEC-2026-07-18-01
Hypothesis: Increasing blocked dependency weight improves SLA hit-rate for medium severity items.
Expected impact: +2–4% resolved_within_sla
Risk: Over-prioritization of dependency-heavy tasks
Rollback if: reopened rate > baseline + 2%
Owner: @qara-os-operator
```

---

## 9) Anti-patterns (do not do)

- Shipping policy changes without outcome data
- Running multiple simultaneous major policy changes (no attribution)
- Keeping knowledge updates in chat only (must be in versioned docs)
- Ignoring overrides (overrides are gold feedback)
- Expanding scope before first loop is stable

---

## 10) 7-day bootstrap checklist

- [ ] Pick first loop (`task-priority-v1`)
- [ ] Define KPI baseline from last 7 days
- [ ] Implement Observe/Act/Measure logging
- [ ] Run first end-to-end cycle
- [ ] Produce first weekly summary
- [ ] Ship one policy update
- [ ] Compare post-change metrics vs baseline

---

## 11) Definition of Done (per cycle)

A cycle is complete only when all are true:

- [ ] Observe, Act, Measure events logged for sampled decisions
- [ ] At least one validated learning note created
- [ ] Knowledge base updated with version bump
- [ ] One decision improvement deployed (or explicit no-change decision documented)
- [ ] KPI comparison published
- [ ] Rollback readiness confirmed

---

## 12) Next iteration (after 2 stable weeks)

Add one additional loop:

- Alert routing, or
- Auto-remediation suggestion ranking, or
- Developer assistance recommendation quality

Keep each loop with separate `loop_id`, KPIs, and policy versions.

